cards.helptext:
Full Address

The full address of a building or site. Use this for recording the address for display purposes.

Building name

The name of the building or site. This should be included if there is no building number, eg. Buckingham Palace.

Building Number

The number of the building, eg. 23, 15A, 1B

Building Number Sub-Street

The number of the building on the sub-street, eg. 23, 15A, 1B

Sub-street

This may be included if the building or site is accessed from a minor street, associated with the main street. This should not be included unless it is essential for identifying the building or site. If it is included then a street must also be included.

Street

The name of the street the building/site is on. In certain cases, for instances in small villages and hamlets, there may be no designated street name and locality should be used, eg. Lover's Cottage, Shelford, Newtown, Madeupshire (where Shelford is the name of the hamlet)

Locality

The name of the locality used for the delivery.

Town or City

The name of the town/city associated with the building or site, eg. Nottingham, Southampton. 

 

Post code

A post code identifies a group of delivery points, eg. NG4 3FN.This should always be included where known. 

Address Status

The status of the address. This will usually be primary for the current address.

From Date

The date from which an address was in use (where known)

To Date

The date up to which an address was in use (where known)

Address Data Qualifier

Used to qualify the period defined by the date range, eg. Ongoing throughout
